___________________________skia___________________________

--------------------------hints--------------------------

You can get ninja from 'github.com/ninja-build/ninja/releases'.
Do not use 'sudo apt-get install ninja', it is not the ninja you need.

Before running [2] make sure to install git.
For Ubuntu: sudo apt-get install git

Older versions of g++ (< 6) will fail while compiling ([5] and [7]).
## For Ubuntu 16.04:
# sudo add-apt-repository -y ppa:jonathonf/gcc
# sudo apt-get update
# sudo apt-get install g++-7
# In [4] and [6] add cc="gcc-7" cxx="g++-7" to --args
# sudo add-apt-repository --remove ppa:jonathonf/gcc
##

In [5] and [7] replace '1' with number of threads you want to use.

-------------------------commands-------------------------
[0] tar xf skia.tar.xz
[1] cd skia
[2] python tools/git-sync-deps
[3] tools/install_dependencies.sh

### Only if you need debug build of enve
# [4] bin/gn gen out/Debug --args='extra_cflags=["-Wno-error"]'
# [5] ninja -C out/Debug -j 1
###

[6] bin/gn gen out/Release --args='is_official_build=true is_debug=false extra_cflags=["-Wno-error"] target_os="linux" target_cpu="x64" skia_use_system_expat=false skia_use_system_freetype2=false skia_use_system_libjpeg_turbo=false skia_use_system_libpng=false skia_use_system_libwebp=false skia_use_system_zlib=false skia_use_system_harfbuzz=false'
[7] ninja -C out/Release -j 1